defaultcard00.name: Pikachu
defaultcard00.description: Pikachu, that can generate powerful electricity, have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.

defaultcard01.name: Charizard
defaultcard01.description: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.

defaultcard02.name: Bulbasaur
defaultcard02.description: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

defaultcard03.name: Squirtle
defaultcard03.description: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

defaultcard04.name: Caterpie
defaultcard04.description: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

defaultcard05.name: Weedle
defaultcard05.description: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

defaultcard06.name: Pidgey
defaultcard06.description: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

defaultcard07.name: Rattata
defaultcard07.description: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

defaultcard08.name: Spearow
defaultcard08.description: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

defaultcard09.name: Ekans
defaultcard09.description: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

65a2cfebf3db7.name: Blastoise
65a2cfebf3db7.description: It crushes its foe under its heavy body to cause fainting. In a pinch, it will withdraw inside its shell.

65a2d861961d7.name: Mew
65a2d861961d7.description: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.
